%20Airlines%20flight%201282%20in%20January%2C%20when%20a%20Boeing%20737%20Max%209%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-airlines-flight-window-portland-oregon-california-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elost%20a%20door%20plug%20in%20midair%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20he%20described%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bwatershed%26quot%3B%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20blowout%2C%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20temporarily%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffaa-grounds-boeing-737-max-9-planes-after-alaska-airlines-incident-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egrounded%20171%20Max%209%20planes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20same%20door%20plug%20and%20ordered%20Boeing%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-ceo-sort-of-glad-faa-paused-expansion-of-737-max-production-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estop%20expanding%20its%20production%20of%20the%20737%20Max%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20eyes%20of%20the%20world%20are%20on%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Calhoun%20wrote%20in%20the%20memo%2C%20emphasizing%20the%20importance%20of%20humility%2C%20%26quot%3Bcomplete%20transparency%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20commitment%20to%20safety%20and%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalhoun%20also%20said%20that%20Boeing%20Chair%20Larry%20Kellner%20wouldn't%20be%20standing%20for%20reelection%2C%20with%20Steve%20Mollenkopf%20elected%20by%20the%20board%20as%20his%20replacement.%20Calhoun%20added%20that%20Stan%20Deal%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Boeing%20Commercial%20Airplanes%2C%20was%20retiring%20and%20would%20be%20replaced%20by%20Stephanie%20Pope%2C%20effective%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalhoun%20became%20the%20company's%20CEO%20and%20president%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.boeing.com%2Fcompany%2Fbios%2Fdavid-l-calhoun%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJanuary%202020%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He'd%20joined%20Boeing's%20board%20in%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERead%20Calhoun's%20full%20memo%20to%20staff%20below.%3Cbr%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3ETeam%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20you%20all%20know%2C%20the%20Alaska%20Airlines%20Flight%201282%20accident%20was%20a%20watershed%20moment%20for%20Boeing.%20We%20must%20continue%20to%20respond%20to%20this%20accident%20with%20humility%20and%20complete%20transparency.%20We%20also%20must%20inculcate%20a%20total%20commitment%20to%20safety%20and%20quality%20at%20every%20level%20of%20our%20company.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20eyes%20of%20the%20world%20are%20on%20us%2C%20and%20I%20know%20we%20will%20come%20through%20this%20moment%20a%20better%20company%2C%20building%20on%20all%20the%20learnings%20we%20accumulated%20as%20we%20worked%20together%20to%20rebuild%20Boeing%20over%20the%20last%20number%20of%20years.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EI%20want%20to%20thank%20each%20and%20every%20one%20of%20you%20for%20how%20you%20have%20stepped%20up%20to%20this%20challenge%20and%20for%20the%20work%20now%20underway%20to%20make%20sure%20we%20demonstrate%20to%20all%20stakeholders%20that%20the%20Boeing%20of%20the%20future%20is%20everything%20they%20should%20expect%20it%20to%20be.%20We%20have%20been%20working%20together%20for%20the%20last%20five%20years%20to%20address%20some%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20challenges%20our%20company%20and%20industry%20have%20ever%20faced%20in%20our%20108-year%20history.%20I%20am%20confident%20that%20the%20way%20we%20have%20confronted%20these%20challenges%2C%20and%20how%20we%20are%20responding%20to%20this%20specific%20moment%2C%20is%20establishing%20standards%20for%20future%20generations%20of%20employees%20and%20will%20be%20woven%20into%20the%20fabric%20of%20how%20we%20operate%20for%20decades%20to%20come.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EIt%20is%20the%20future%20of%20our%20company%20that%20is%20the%20subject%20of%20my%20letter%20to%20you%20today.%20I%20have%20been%20considering%20for%20some%20time%2C%20in%20discussion%20with%20our%20board%20of%20directors%2C%20the%20right%20time%20for%20a%20CEO%20transition%20at%20Boeing.%20I%20want%20to%20share%20with%20you%20that%20I%20have%20decided%20this%20will%20be%20my%20last%20year%20as%20CEO%20of%20our%20great%20company%2C%20and%20I%20have%20notified%20the%20board%20of%20that%20decision.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EI%20originally%20agreed%20to%20take%20on%20the%20role%20of%20CEO%20of%20Boeing%20at%20the%20board's%20request%2C%20stepping%20down%20as%20board%20chair%20in%20the%20process%2C%20because%20of%20the%20unprecedented%20circumstances%20the%20company%20was%20facing%20at%20that%20time.%20It%20has%20been%20the%20greatest%20privilege%20of%20my%20life%20to%20serve%20in%20both%20roles%20and%20I%20will%20only%20feel%20the%20journey%20has%20been%20properly%20completed%20when%20we%20finish%20the%20job%20that%20we%20need%20to%20do.%20We%20are%20going%20to%20fix%20what%20isn't%20working%2C%20and%20we%20are%20going%20to%20get%20our%20company%20back%20on%20the%20track%20towards%20recovery%20and%20stability.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EMy%20decision%20to%20step%20down%20as%20CEO%20at%20the%20end%20of%20this%20year%20is%20one%20the%20board%20has%20been%20prepared%20for%20and%20will%20result%20in%20a%20number%20of%20changes%20at%20a%20management%20and%20governance%20level%20moving%20forward.%20My%20long-time%20partner%20in%20all%20things%20Boeing%2C%20our%20Chair%20Larry%20Kellner%2C%20has%20advised%20the%20board%20and%20me%20that%20he%20does%20not%20intend%20to%20stand%20for%20re-election%20at%20our%20upcoming%20Annual%20Meeting%20of%20Shareholders.%20The%20board%20has%20elected%20Steve%20Mollenkopf%20to%20succeed%20Larry%20as%20chair.%20Steve%20will%20lead%20the%20board%20process%20of%20selecting%20my%20successor%20as%20CEO.%20Larry%2C%20too%2C%20had%20been%20considering%20the%20appropriate%20moment%20to%20turn%20over%20the%20reins%20after%20more%20than%20four%20years%20as%20chair%20and%2013%20years%20on%20our%20board%2C%20and%20concluded%20that%20the%20CEO%20selection%20process%20should%20be%20led%20by%20a%20chair%20who%20will%20stay%20at%20the%20helm%20as%20a%20partner%20to%20the%20new%20CEO.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EI%20want%20to%20express%20my%20deepest%20personal%20thanks%20to%20Larry%20for%20his%20outstanding%20leadership%20over%20the%20last%20number%20of%20years%2C%20and%20I%20know%20I%20speak%20for%20everyone%20at%20the%20company%20when%20I%20say%2C%20nobody%20could%20have%20worked%20harder%20or%20longer%20hours%20in%20dedication%20to%20his%20duties.%20Perhaps%20first%2C%20among%20the%20many%20legacies%20of%20his%20tenure%2C%20is%20profoundly%20strengthened%20governance%20at%20our%20company%2C%20including%20through%20his%20recruitment%20of%20several%20superb%20new%20board%20members%2C%20and%20his%20work%20with%20others%20on%20the%20board%20to%20establish%20our%20independent%20standing%20board%20aerospace%20safety%20committee.%20Larry%20is%20a%20professional%20in%20every%20way%20and%20someone%20to%20whom%20Boeing%20owes%20a%20great%20debt%20of%20gratitude.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EI%20also%20want%20to%20thank%20Steve%20for%20his%20willingness%20to%20take%20on%20the%20role%20as%20chair.%20Steve%20has%20had%20a%20long%20and%20extraordinarily%20successful%20career%20with%20decades%20of%20experience%20as%20both%20a%20CEO%20of%20Qualcomm%20and%20a%20board%20member%20of%20several%20important%20public%20companies.%20Since%20joining%20the%20Boeing%20board%2C%20his%20contribution%20has%20been%20extremely%20valuable%20and%20his%20professional%20background%20as%20an%20engineer%20will%20serve%20him%20and%20the%20company%20well%20in%20this%20new%20role.%20I%20look%20forward%20to%20working%20with%20him%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20this%20year%20to%20ensure%20a%20smooth%20transition.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20addition%20to%20these%20changes%2C%20Boeing%20Commercial%20Airplanes%20President%20and%20Chief%20Executive%20Officer%20Stan%20Deal%20will%20retire%20from%20the%20company%20and%20Stephanie%20Pope%20will%20lead%20our%20BCA%20business%2C%20effective%20today.%20I%20want%20to%20thank%20Stan%20for%20his%20many%20contributions%20and%20dedication%20since%20first%20joining%20our%20ranks%2038%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20for%20his%20tireless%20service%20as%20our%20BCA%20leader%20during%20an%20uncommonly%20difficult%20period%20for%20our%20company%20and%20for%20our%20industry.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EI%20also%20want%20to%20thank%20Stephanie%20for%20taking%20on%20this%20critical%20role.%20With%20nearly%2030%20years%20of%20experience%20at%20Boeing%2C%20including%20her%20successful%20tenure%20leading%20our%20global%20services%20business%2C%20Stephanie%20knows%20our%20company%20inside%20and%20out%20and%20has%20a%20proven%20track%20record%20of%20superb%20leadership%2C%20including%20an%20innate%20talent%20for%20listening%20and%20responding%20to%20our%20people.%20Stephanie%20is%20a%20third-generation%20Boeing%20employee.%20She%20is%20deeply%20committed%20to%20our%20company%2C%20to%20our%20employees%20and%20to%20our%20shared%20future%3B%20and%20she%20is%20the%20perfect%20person%20to%20take%20on%20the%20leadership%20of%20our%20commercial%20airplanes%20business%20at%20this%20moment.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20we%20begin%20this%20period%20of%20transition%2C%20I%20want%20to%20assure%20you%2C%20we%20will%20remain%20squarely%20focused%20on%20completing%20the%20work%20we%20have%20done%20together%20to%20return%20our%20company%20to%20stability%20after%20the%20extraordinary%20challenges%20of%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20with%20safety%20and%20quality%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20everything%20that%20we%20do.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EThank%20you%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EDave%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-ceo-steps-down-read-dave-calhoun-staff-memo-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711369728000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66016ccf1caec1275a68e048%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-ceo-steps-down-read-dave-calhoun-staff-memo-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Boeing%20CEO%20Dave%20Calhoun%20said%20Monday%20that%20he%20is%20stepping%20down%20from%20the%20role%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22gdean%40businessinsider.com%20(Grace%20Dean%2CTaylor%20Rains)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A45%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-ceo-steps-down-read-dave-calhoun-staff-memo-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ray%20of%20light%20for%20Ishan%20as%20BCCI%20secretary%20chats%20with%20him%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711369645000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108768276%2Cimgsize-133732.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fipl%2Ftop-stories%2Fray-of-light-for-out-of-favour-ishan-kishan-as-bcci-secretary-chats-with-him-post-ipl-game%2Farticleshow%2F108768261.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ishan%20Kishan%2C%20who%20was%20recently%20dropped%20from%20BCCI's%20central%20contract%20list%2C%20had%20secretary%20Jay%20Shah%20chatting%20up%20with%20him%20on%20Sunday%20evening%20after%20Mumbai%20Indians'%20IPL%20game%2C%20a%20gesture%20which%20could%20be%20viewed%20as%20silver%20lining%20for%20the%20maverick%20wicketkeeper-batter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%2