cial-network-301377197.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacquired%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fglassdoor-company-bowls-anonymous-workplace-forum-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGlassdoor%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20since%20changed%20its%20terms%20of%20service%20to%20require%20all%20users%20to%20be%20verified%20by%20adding%20their%20names%20and%20jobs%20to%20their%20profiles.%20Its%20help%20page%20says%20it%20%26quot%3Bwill%20never%20share%20your%20personal%20information%20without%20your%20permission.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20person's%20full%20name%20on%20their%20profile%20cannot%20be%20seen%20by%20others%2C%20but%20users%20can%20choose%20to%20display%20their%20name%20when%20posting%20a%20review%2C%20or%20remain%20anonymous.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20new%20users%20now%20sign%20up%20to%20the%20platform%2C%20they%20are%20asked%20to%20provide%20their%20full%20name%2C%20job%20title%20and%20employer.%20Previously%20only%20an%20email%20address%20was%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJosh%20Thieler%2C%20a%20longtime%20Glassdoor%20user%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20changes%20were%20a%20%26quot%3Bbetrayal%20of%20trust%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20he'd%20closed%20his%20account.%20%26quot%3BI%20removed%20my%20posts%20and%20deleted%20my%20account%20to%20signal%20to%20Glassdoor%20that%20I%20will%20not%20support%20their%20decision%20to%20reverse%20course%20and%20destroy%20the%20anonymity%20of%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20workers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGlassdoor%20warns%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrtechprivacy.com%2Fbrands%2Fglassdoor%23privacypolicy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprivacy%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2C%20as%20it%20collects%20more%20personal%20data%20about%20users%20that%20is%20displayed%20publicly%2C%20there%20could%20be%20instances%20that%20its%20mechanisms%20to%20protect%20users'%20anonymity%20%26quot%3Baren't%20perfect.%26quot%3