nd%20secure%20a%20substantial%20portion%20of%20the%20parliamentary%20seats%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%2C%20which%20is%20ruling%20at%20the%20national%20level%2C%20has%20strategically%20forged%20alliances%20with%20smaller%20regional%20parties%20to%20make%20inroads%20into%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20political%20landscape.%20Historically%20lacking%20influence%20in%20the%20state%2C%20the%20BJP%20aims%20to%20broaden%20its%20reach%20by%20collaborating%20with%20local%20entities%20and%20establishing%20a%20foothold.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Anna%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(AIADMK)%2C%20one%20of%20the%20principal%20opposition%20parties%20in%20the%20state%2C%20grapples%20with%20internal%20divisions.%20Despite%20its%20significant%20presence%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20politics%2C%20internal%20factions%20within%20the%20party%20pose%20it%20a%20formidable%20challenge.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20AIADMK%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20contest%20separately%20from%20the%20BJP%20adds%20complexity%20to%20the%20electoral%20equation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStrategically%20positioning%20itself%2C%20the%20BJP%20seeks%20to%20capitalise%20on%20the%20void%20left%20by%20the%20AIADMK%20by%20contesting%20independently%2C%20aiming%20to%20emerge%20as%20a%20credible%20alternative%20and%20secure%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20seats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDravidian%20dominance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20political%20landscape%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20has%20long%20been%20dominated%20by%20the%20DMK%20and%20the%20AIADMK%2C%20a%20phenomenon%20that%20is%20rooted%20in%20the%20Dravidian%20movement%2C%20which%20champions%20social%20justice%2C%20linguistic%20pride%20and%20regional%20autonomy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20parties%20resonate%20with%20voters%20through%20identity-driven%20issues%2C%20caste%20dynamics%20and%20a%20shared%20cultural%20heritage%2C%20which%20are%20further%20amplified%20by%20the%20influence%20of%20cinematic%20icons%20like%20M.G.%20Ramachandran%20and%20J.%20Jayalalithaa.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fhow-the-dravidian-model-of-development-succeeded-in-tamil-nadu%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20Dravidian%20Model%20of%20Development%20Succeeded%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20alliance%20spectrum%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20state%20gears%20up%20for%20the%20forthcoming%20general%20election%2C%20three%20major%20alliances%20centre%20stage.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20led%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20by%20M.K.%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20DMK%2C%20includes%20the%20INC%2C%20the%20Vaiyapuri%20Gopalsamy-led%20Marumalarchi%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(MDMK)%2C%20the%20Viduthalai%20Chiruthaigal%20Katchi%20(VCK)%2C%20the%20Indian%20Union%20Muslim%20League%20and%20smaller%20regional%20entities%2C%20emphasising%20diversity%20and%20a%20commitment%20to%20secularism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20AIADMK%20alliance%2C%20despite%20internal%20strife%20following%20Jayalalithaa%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20is%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0a%20coalition%20with%20various%20parties%2C%20including%20the%20Desiya%20Murpokku%20Dravida%20Kazhagam%20(DMDK)%2C%20Puthiya%20Tamizhagam%20(PT)%20and%20Social%20Democratic%20Party%20of%20India%20(SDPI).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%2C%20spearheaded%20by%20the%20BJP%2C%20includes%20the%20Pattali%20Makkal%20Katchi%20(PMK)%2C%20the%20Tamil%20Maanila%20Congress%20and%20the%20Amma%20Makkal%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(AMMK)%2C%20which%20is%20a%20breakaway%20faction%20of%20the%20AIADMK%20led%20by%20T.T.V.%20Dhinakaran.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20aim%20to%20extend%20their%20influence%20through%20collaborations%2C%20highlighting%20a%20broad%20spectrum%20of%20political%20alliances%20vying%20for%20dominance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrevious%20election%E2%80%99s%20analysis%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReflecting%20on%20past%20election%20analyses%2C%20significant%20contests%20in%202009%2C%202014%20and%202019%20underscored%20the%20dynamic%20nature%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20political%20landscape.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKey%20factors%20contributing%20to%20electoral%20outcomes%20include%20charismatic%20leadership%2C%20effective%20governance%20and%20strategic%20alliances.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202009%2C%20a%20fierce%20contest%20unfolded%20between%20the%20DMK-led%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20(UPA)%20(INC%2C%20VCK%20and%20IUML)%20and%20the%20AIADMK-led%20Third%20Front%20(the%20PMK%2C%20MDMK%2C%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(CPI)%20and%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20Marxist%20(CPI(M))).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Faiadmk-bjp-split-what-lies-ahead-tamil-nadu%5C%22%3EAIADMK-BJP%20Split%3A%20What%20Lies%20Ahead%20for%20Politics%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20at%20the%20National%20Level%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20pre-election%20polls%20favouring%20the%20AIADMK%2C%20the%20UPA%20secured%20an%20unexpected%20victory%20with%2027%20out%20of%2039%20seats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202014%2C%20the%20AIADMK%20clinched%20a%20resounding%20victory%20by%20securing%2037%20seats.%20The%20electoral%C2%A0%20landscape%20featured%20a%20showdown%20among%20the%20AIADMK%2C%20the%20NDA%20(including%20the%20BJP%2C%20DMDK%20and%20PMK)%2C%20the%20Democratic%20Progressive%20Alliance%20(DMK%2C%20VCK%2C%20IUML%2C%20MK%2C%20PT)%2C%20the%20INC%20and%20the%20Left%20and%20Secular%20alliance%20(CPI%20and%20CPI%20(M)).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20NDA%20captured%20the%20remaining%20two%20seats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202019%2C%20the%20Secular%20Progressive%20Alliance%20(SPA)%20led%20by%20the%20DMK%2C%20and%20the%20NDA%20led%20by%20the%20AIADMK%2C%20vied%20for%20supremacy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20SPA%20secured%20a%20commanding%20victory%20with%2038%20seats%2C%20while%20the%20NDA%20managed%20only%20one%20seat%2C%20won%20by%20the%20AIADMK.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20demise%20of%20J.%20Jayalalithaa%20in%202016%20posed%20challenges%20for%20the%20AIADMK%2C%20which%20the%20DMK%20under%20M.K.%20Stalin%20capitalised%20on.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F25135006%2FVS_partyimage1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22748%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F25135006%2FVS_partyimage1.jpg%20748w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F25135006%2FVS_partyimage1-300x171.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-703137%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22427%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChart%20by%20author.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECaste%20dynamics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECaste%20dynamics%20also%20play%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20politics%2C%20with%20various%20communities%20wielding%20influence%20and%20shaping%20political%20affiliations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Mukkulathor%20community%2C%20comprising%20about%2011.7%25%20of%20the%20populace%2C%20holds%20considerable%20sway%20particul