es.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E2.%20%3Cstrong%3ENewly%20minted%20%E2%80%93%20often%20months-old%20%E2%80%93%20companies%2C%20have%20contributed%20huge%20amounts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20to%20parties%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fdata%2Fnew-firms-bought-crores-of-electoral-bonds-within-months-formation%2Farticle67958808.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cat%20least%2043%20firms%20newly%20incorporated%20in%20the%20year%202018%20or%20later%20have%20bought%C2%A0electoral%20bonds%C2%A0worth%20over%20Rs%20384.5%20crore.%E2%80%9D%20Of%20them%2C%20four%20companies%2C%20all%20established%20in%202023%20in%20Hyderabad%2C%20bought%20bonds%20worth%20crores%20of%20rupees%2C%20within%20months%20of%20being%20established.%20Nine%20firms%20in%202020%20and%20eleven%20companies%20in%202021%20were%20formed%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20cumulatively%20purchased%20bonds%20worth%20close%20to%20Rs%20100%20crore%2C%20%E2%80%9Cin%20just%20one%20or%20two%20years%20after%20getting%20formed.%E2%80%9D%20Were%20the%20firms%20started%20with%20the%20sole%20purpose%20of%20paying%20money%20to%20certain%20parties%20has%20to%20be%20probed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E3.%20Companies%20which%20were%20awarded%20%3Cstrong%3Emajor%20contracts%20coinciding%20with%20their%20purchase%20of%20electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20The%20%E2%80%98quid%20pro%20quo%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmegha-engineering-made-some-electoral-bond-purchases-close-to-bagging-contracts-5291971%5C%22%3Emove%3C%2Fa%3E%20deserves%20an%20enquiry%20under%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act%20(POCA).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E4.%20%3Cstrong%3ECompanies%20which%20have%20donated%20money%20via%20electoral%20bonds%20only%20after%20they%20were%20raided%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20by%20agencies%20like%20the%20ED%2C%20CBI%20and%20IT%2C%20and%20the%20cases%20against%20them%20have%20either%20stalled%20or%20withdrawn.%20An%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Fnews%2Ftnm-nl-investigation-30-firms-facing-ed-it-probe-donated-rs-335-cr-to-bjp%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einvestigation%20in%20February%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20found%20that%2030%20firms%20facing%20ED%2C%20IT%20probes%20%E2%80%9Cdonated%20Rs%20335%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2F18-of-19-firms-marked-high-risk-by-finance-ministry-that-bought-electoral-bonds-went-off-future-list%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20companies%20cited%20as%20dubious%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%E2%80%99s%20Financial%20Intelligence%20Unit%20(FIU)%2C%20donating%20significant%20sums%20as%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20also%20coincidentally%20making%20their%20way%20out%20of%20the%20lists%20by%20the%20ministry%20in%20subsequent%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E5.%20Redemption%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20by%20a%20party%20%3Cstrong%3Eeven%20after%20their%20expiry%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20In%20order%20to%20allow%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20to%20encash%20expired%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2010%20crore%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20broke%20the%20official%20rules%20on%20the%20eve%20of%202018%20Karnataka%20assembly%20elections%2C%20as%20per%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reporters-collective.in%2Ftrc%2Fmodi-govt-allowed-bjp-to-illegally-encash-expired-bonds%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Eby%20The%20Reporters%E2%80%99%20Collective.%20This%20needs%20investigation%2C%20and%20those%20who%20broke%20the%20law%20should%20be%20identified%20and%20prosecuted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E6.%20The%20%3Cstrong%3Eclaims%20made%20by%20SBI%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20that%20it%20did%20not%20maintain%20matching%20data%2C%20or%20needed%20till%20June%2030%20to%20provide%20the%20data%2C%20deserves%20a%20probe%20to%20investigate%20the%20motives%20behind%20their%20attempt%20to%20mislead%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20former%20Election%20Commissioner%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Felectoral-bond-law-ashok-lavasa-sbi-data%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAshok%20Lavasa%20wrote%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20shortly%20before%20the%20SBI%20furnished%20the%20data%2C%20there%20were%20mixed%20signals%20emanating%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20leading%20public%20sector%20bank.%20He%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20while%20Section%207(4)%20of%20The%20(now%20scrapped)%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20(EBS)%2C%202018%2C%20said%20that%20information%20furnished%20by%20the%20buyer%20%E2%80%9Cshall%20be%20treated%20confidential%20by%20the%20authorised%20bank%20and%20shall%20not%20be%20disclosed%20to%20any%20authority%20for%20any%20purposes%2C%20except%20when%20demanded%20by%20a%20competent%20court%20or%20upon%20registration%20of%20criminal%20case%20by%20any%20law%20enforcement%20agency%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98designers%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20EBS%C2%A0are%20also%20saying%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20the%20bank%20could%20not%20have%20legally%20kept%20any%20record%20of%20the%20secret%20number%20on%20the%20bond%20issued%20to%20the%20purchaser%20(in%20keeping%20with%20the%20provision%20of%20anonymity%20enshrined%20in%20the%20EBS).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20this%20is%20the%20case%2C%20it%20would%20be%20almost%20impossible%20to%20establish%20any%20link%20between%20purchaser%20and%20recipient.%E2%80%9D%20Lavasa%20is%20saying%20this%20inconsistency%20is%20critical.%20If%20the%20bank%20is%20now%20saying%20that%20the%20bond%20was%20%E2%80%9Cakin%20to%20currency%E2%80%9D%2C%20then%20%E2%80%9Chow%20could%20SBI%2C%20when%20forced%20to%20disclosed%20to%20an%20enforcement%20agency%2C%20reveal%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20purchaser%20but%20limit%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20investigations%20only%20to%20the%20sources%20of%20funds%3F%20Does%20this%20not%20rule%20out%20the%20possibility%20of%20providing%20the%20donor-political%20party%20link%2C%20thereby%20eliminating%20the%20clue%20that%20would%20be%20vital%20to%20probe%20allegations%20of%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFormer%20Finance%20Secretary%20S.C.%20Garg%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fsbi-recording-unique-number-of-electoral-bonds-completely-unlawful-former-finance-secretary-subhash-garg-report-11711205187720.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehas%20added%20a%20double%20twist%20to%20this%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20weekend%2C%20by%20castigating%20SBI%20for%20recording%20the%20unique%20alpha-numeric.%20He%20termed%20the%20bank%E2%80%99s%20actions%20in%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case%20%E2%80%9Ccompletely%20unlawful%20and%20unexpected%E2%80%9D.%20Speaking%20with%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EIndian%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EExpress%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Garg%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CDoing%20so%2C%20it%20%5BSBI%5D%20had%20violated%20the%20anonymity%20promised%20to%20donors%20under%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%2C%202018.%E2%80%9D%20It%20is%20the%20bond%20numbers%20that%20have%20enabled%20a%20match%20between%20the%20purchasers%20of%20the%20bonds%20with%20the%20political%20parties%20that%20encashed%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20SBI%20must%20answer%20for%20inconsistencies%20in%20its%20position%20and%20statements%20to%20the%20court.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E7.%20The%20%3Cstrong%3EElection%20Commission%20also%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felection-commission-has-no-comments-on-landmark-verdict-on-electoral-bonds-how-it-changed-its-stance%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3Edilly-dallied%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20on%20t