%20of%20no-objection%20certificates%20or%20NOCs%20for%20the%20sale%20of%20land%20between%20people%20belonging%20to%20different%20religions%20for%20three%20months%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fother-states%2Fassam-suspends-noc-for-sale-of-land-between-people-of-different-religions-for-three-months%2Farticle67979389.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20notes%20that%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20Revenue%20and%20Disaster%20Management%20(Registration)%20Department%20issued%20a%20notification%20on%20March%207%20through%20the%20state%20governor%2C%20saying%20that%20this%20pause%20comes%20after%20inputs%20from%20intelligence%20agencies%20which%20have%20allegedly%20pointed%20to%20the%20transfer%20of%20land%20involving%20people%20of%20different%20religions%20%E2%80%9Cby%20fraudulent%20means.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVested%20interests%20can%20thus%20create%20communal%20conflict%20with%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20ahead%2C%20the%20notification%20claims%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20notification%20however%20adds%20that%20if%20a%20district%20commissioner%20notes%20that%20a%20no-objection%20certificate%20is%20%E2%80%9Cabsolutely%20necessary%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20not%20lead%20to%20any%20breach%20of%20law%20and%20order%2C%E2%80%9D%20then%20it%20can%20be%20issued%20with%20prior%20concurrence%20of%20the%20Assam%20Inspector%20General%20of%20Registration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20notification%20is%20signed%20by%20Gyanendra%20Dev%20Tripathi%2C%20the%20Principal%20Secretary%20to%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20Revenue%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELok%20Sabha%20elections%20in%2014%20constituencies%20in%20Assam%20will%20be%20conducted%20in%20three%20phases%2C%20on%20April%2019%2C%20April%2026%2C%20and%20May%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20notification%20follows%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20third%20phase%20of%20the%20Himanta%20government%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20Mission%20Basundhara%20under%20which%20only%20%E2%80%9Cindigenous%E2%80%9D%20people%20of%20Assam%20can%20apply%20to%20get%20land%20titles%20for%20government-owned%20lands.%20Himanta%20had%20earlier%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fislamphobia-statecraft-assam-himanta-biswa-sarma%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Bengali-origin%20Muslims%20who%20are%20landless%20could%20not%20apply%20for%20land%20under%20this%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711283425000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F23221556%2F2022_11img23_Nov_2022_PTI11_23_2022_000240B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fassam-pauses-noc-for-sale-of-land-between-people-of-different-religions%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20government%20has%20cited%20inputs%20from%20intelligence%20agencies%20which%20have%20allegedly%20pointed%20to%20the%20transfer%20of%20land%20involving%20people%20of%20different%20religions%20'by%20fraudulent%20means'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fassam-pauses-noc-for-sale-of-land-between-people-of-different-religions%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Questionable%3A%20What%20Kind%20of%20Government%20Do%20Indians%20Want%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F24172220%2FIndiya-but-bigger.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20that%2C%20a%20fresh%20spate%20of%20renamings%20and%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20new%20list%20of%20%E2%80%98ferocious%E2%80%99%20dog%20breeds%2C%20have%20you%20kept%20up%20with%20the%20news%20as%20of%20late%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSeffGw_mZZPMetWYN8nF1xuB1eogL2KAEF3HKhRHn2fmKydvA%2Fviewform%3Fembedded%3Dtrue%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224077%5C%22%3ELoading%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711282237000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F24172220%2FIndiya-but-bigger.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fquiz%2Fquestionable-what-kind-of-government-do-indians-want%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Between%20that%2C%20a%20fresh%20spate%20of%20renamings%20and%20the%20government's%20new%20list%20of%20'ferocious'%20dog%20breeds%2C%20have%20you%20kept%20up%20with%20the%20news%20as%20of%20late%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fquiz%2Fquestionable-what-kind-of-government-do-indians-want%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Simultaneous%20Elections%20Will%20Be%20a%20Blow%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20Popular%20Sovereignty%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F29135301%2FScreenshot-2024-02-29-at-1.52.52-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Ramnath%20Kovind%20committee%2C%20constituted%20on%20September%202%2C%202023%2C%20to%20operationalise%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20desire%20of%20%E2%80%98one%20nation%2C%20one%20election%E2%80%99%20(ONOE)%2C%20an%20oxymoron%20for%20simultaneous%20elections%20at%20each%20of%20the%20three%20levels%20of%20representative%20government%20in%20India%2C%20has%20fulfilled%20his%20bidding.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20prime%20minister%20has%20been%20expressing%20his%20fancy%20about%20it%20ever%20since%20he%20came%20to%20power%20in%202014.%20In%20recommending%20%E2%80%98ONOE%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%2018%2C600%20page%20report%2C%20put%20together%20following%20a%20191%20day%20consultation%2C%20presented%20on%20March%2014%2C%202024%2C%20it%20has%20fulfilled%20its%20obligation.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Kovind%20committee%20will%20go%20down%20in%20the%20history%20of%20Indian%20democracy%20as%20a%20rare%20committee%20that%20was%20asked%20to%20find%20ways%20of%20implementing%20a%20fanciful%2C%20but%20unconstitutional%2C%20idea%20rather%20than%20examining%20an%20issue%2C%20which%20it%20obediently%20did.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20former%20president%2C%20Kovind%20should%20have%20kept%20out%20of%20this%20contentious%20and%20unconstitutional%20issue.%20A%20President%20of%20India%2C%20particularly%20one%20who%20has%20had%20no%20independent%20political%20status%20or%20eminence%20before%20being%20airdropped%20on%20this%20prestigious%20chair%20due%20to%20personal%20loyalty%2C%20should%20at%20least%20be%20left%20with%20the%20honour%20of%20being%20a%20distinguished%20citizen%20beyond%20the%20contentious%20muddied%20politics%20of%20the%20country.%20Indeed%2C%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20and%20later%20her%20party%2C%20invented%20and%20operated%20with%20a%20loyalist%20president%2C%20but%20since%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20revered%20and%20projected%20as%20a%20millennial%20politician-statesman%2C%20he%20could%20have%20spared%20the%20Rashtrapati%20Bhawan%20from%20being%20his%20loyalists%E2%80%99%20domain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20result%20of%20the%20Kovind%20committee%20that%20had%20two%20ministers%20of%20the%20Modi%20cabinet%20%E2%80%93%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20and%20law%20minister%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal%20%E2%80%93%20along%20with%20other%20saffron%20loyalists%2C%20was%20a%20foregone%20conclusion%3B%20only%20modalities%20had%20to%20be%20suggested%20to%20wrap%20it%20in%20a%20shroud%20of%20a%20consultative%20exercise.%C2%A0%20It%20was%20obviously%20not%20an%20independent%2C%20but%20a%20guided%20panel.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EModalities%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20committee%20begins%20with%20a%20statement%20on%20%E2%80%98restoration%E2%80%99%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%2C%20as%20if%20simultaneous%20elections%20began%20with%20a%20design%20and%20a%20statutory%20mandate.%20The%20beginning%20of%20the%20election%20process%20in%20India%20in%201951-52%20was%20%E2%80%98simultaneous%E2%80%99%20not%20by%20design.%20Since%20elections%20were%20conducted%20only%20at%20the%20two%20constitutionally%20designed%20levels%20of%20representative%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20to%20elect%20the%20first%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20Vidhan%20Sabhas%2C%20each%20for%20a%20term%20of%20five%20years%2C%20simultaneity%20became%20ingrained%2C%20and%20stayed%20for%20a%20decade%20and%20a%20half.%C2%A0%20Obviously%2C%20as%20long%20as%20these%20elected%20houses%20completed%20their%20designated%20full%20five-year%20term%2C%20the%20five-year%20cycle%20of%20simultaneousness%20remained.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20the%20framers%20of%20the%20constitution%20did%20not%20prescribe%20any%20compulsive%20modality%20to%20maintain%20the%20cycle%20at%20both%20the%20levels%20meant%20that%20in%20case%20of%20a%20premature%20dissolution%20of%20a%20house%20mid-term%20poll%20for%20a%20new%20house%20with%20a%20five-year%20term%20in%20the%20Westminster%20tradition%20was%20agreed%20by%20all.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Kovind%20committee%E2%80%99s%20contention%20that%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20cycle%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%2C%20which%20was%20disrupted%20after%20the%20initial%20decades%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20independence%E2%80%99%20stresses%20a%20non-existent%20abnormality%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20process.%20Defined%20by%20Articles%2083(2)%20and%20172(1)%2C%20the%20elections%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20Vidhan%20Sabhas%20are%20for%20five%20years%20%E2%80%98unless%20sooner%20dissolved%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%20Obviously%2C%20the%20framers%20of%20the%20Constitution%20did%20not%20see%20any%20abnormality%20if%20a%20house%20was%20dissolved%20earlier.%C2%A0%20In%20fact%2C%20Article%2083(2)%20foresees%20a%20possibility%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20term%20extended%20for%20a%20year%20(at%20a%20time)%20and%20%E2%80%98not%20extending%20in%20any%20case%20beyond%20a%20period%20of%20six%20months%20after%20the%20Proclamation%20has%20ceased%20to%20operate.%E2%80%99%C2%A0%20Article%20172(1)%20unambiguously%20prescribes%20the%20same%20term%20for%20the%20Legislative%20Assemblies%20of%20the%20states.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fone-nation-one-election-further-weaken-democracy%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election%E2%80%99%20Will%20Further%20Weaken%20Indian%20Democracy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20third%20tier%20of%20the%20Indian%20democracy%20was%20not%20clearly%20defined%20till%20the%2073%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erd%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%2074%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20constitutional%20amendments%20became%20laws%20in%20April%201993.%20Article%20243E%20and%20243U%20make%20similar%20provisions%20for%20panchayats%20in%20rural%20areas%20and%20municipalities%20in%20urban%20areas.%20The%20irregularity%20of%20their%20elections%20in%20all%20the%20states%20irrespective%20of%20the%20party%20in%20power%20reflects%20how%20the%20grassroots%20institutions%20have%20been%20treated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDisruptions%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20has%20been%20described%20as%20%E2%80%98disruption%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20committee%20was%20ingrained%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20development%20since%20the%20electoral%20process%20was%20set%20in%20motion.%20Though%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Kerala%20assembly%20in%201960%2C%20by%20imposing%20Article%20356%2C%20was%20the%20first%20sign%2C%20the%20first%20major%20%E2%80%98disruption%E2%80%99%20came%20in%20the%20fourth%20general%20elections%20in%201967%20due%20to%20a%20weakened%20Congress%20and%20underdeveloped%20opposition%20system.%20In%20fact%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20party%20system%20just%20began%20reconfiguring.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWherever%20a%20stable%20alternative%20emerged%2C%20for%20example%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20the%20electoral%20process%20stabilised.%20But%20the%20unstable%20party%20alteration%20in%20the%20northern%20states%2C%20that%20gave%20birth%20to%20ephemeral%20coalitions%2C%20characterized%20by%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eaaya%20ram%2C%20gaya%20ram%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20(defectors)%20and%20%E2%80%98suitcase%E2%80%99%20(money)%20politics.%20State%20Legislative%20Assemblies%20were%20dissolved%20without%20completing%20their%20term.%20These%20imbalances%20later%20led%20to%20a%20fractured%20party%20system.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELok%20Sabha%E2%80%99s%20first%20mid-term%20dissolution%20in%201971%2C%20de-coupled%20the%20two%20levels%20of%20polls.%20The%20Emergency%20in%201975%20perpetuated%20the%20disequilibrium.%20After%20that%2C%20synchronisation%20could%20not%20be%20achieved%20because%20elected%20in%201977%2C%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20was%20dissolved%20again%20in%201980.%20And%20before%20that%20state%20assemblies%20were%20dissolved%20and%20re-elected%20in%201978.%20On%20her%20return%20in%201980%2C%20Gandhi%20too%20dissolved%20the%20state%20assemblies%20and%20re-elected%20them%20in%201982.%20The%20disruption%20of%20any%20possibility%20of%20simultaneity%20thus%20happened%20due%20to%20dynamics%20of%20political%20processes%20and%20the%20undemocratic%20use%20of%20Article%20356%20of%20the%20Constitution%20by%20ruling%20parties%20at%20the%20centre%20till%20the%20Bommai%20judgment%20in%201994.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EConstitutionally%20De-creasing%20the%20Democratic%20Process%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20recommending%20the%20artificial%20process%20of%20%E2%80%98de-creasing%E2%80%99%20the%20democratic%20and%20constitutional%20processes%2C%20the%20Kovind%20committee%20recommends%20a%20two-step%20process%20beginning%20with%20synchronisation%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20Assemblies%20followed%20by%20municipalities%20and%20panchayats.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20recommendation%20that%20the%20tenure%20of%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%20should%20end%20with%20the%20subsequent%20general%20elections%20to%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%2C%20after%20the%20%E2%80%98appointed%E2%80%99%20date%2C%20has%20a%20compelled%20artificiality.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20committee%20introduces%20two%20new%20terms%20in%20the%20lexicon%20of%20parliamentary%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20unexpired%20term%20and%20full%20term.%20The%20former%20to%20be%20used%20in%20case%20a%20house%20is%20dissolved%20earlier%20than%20five%20years%20and%20the%20latter%20if%20a%20house%20completes%20its%20full%20five-year%20term.%C2%A0%20The%20committee%20proposes%20to%20amend%20the%20constitution%20to%20make%20these%20concepts%20parts%20of%20the%20statute.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EObviously%2C%20in%20this%20new%20electoral%20scheme%2C%20an%20elected%20house%20would%20get%20a%20five-year%20or%20%E2%80%98full%20term%E2%80%99%20not%20only%20because%20it%20has%20been%20elected%20for%20that%20term%2C%20but%20only%20if%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20also%20completes%20its%20%E2%80%98full%20term%E2%80%99.%20The%20full%20term%20of%20five%20years%20thus%20will%20not%20begin%20from%20the%20day%20of%20the%20constitution%20of%20a%20house%20after%20election%2C%20but%20a%20pre-determined%20date%20decided%20following%20suggested%20constitutional%20amendments.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20a%20proposed%20transitory%20period%20till%20synchronisation%20is%20achieved.%20The%20report%20also%20talks%20of%20a%20possibility%20that%20elections%20are%20not%20held%20simultaneously%2C%20in%20such%20a%20case%20an%20order%20on%20presidential%20advice%20would%20be%20issued%20to%20hold%20a%20particular%20election%20at%20a%20later%20date.%20In%20short%2C%20the%20whole%20scheme%20proposes%20an%20unnecessary%20tampering%20with%20the%20constitution%20and%20electoral%20process.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPopular%20Sovereignty%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EElections%20operationalise%20and%20legitimise%20popular%20sovereignty%20for%20different%20levels%20of%20government.%20Obviously%2C%20simultaneity%20of%20elections%20at%20different%20tiers%20of%20government%20may%20not%20necessarily%20add%20to%20democratic%20spirit.%20A%20compulsive%20tying%20up%20of%20the%20lower%20levels%20elections%20with%20the%20higher%20tiers%20would%20have%20the%20impact%20of%20fudging%20of%20the%20issues%20that%20are%20raised%20at%20appropriate%20levels.%20The%20voters%20assert%20their%20democratic%20rights%20and%20entitlements%20by%20raising%20and%20asserting%20their%20sovereign%20will.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20proposed%20synchronisation%20up%20may%20be%20good%20for%20a%20particular%20regime%20%E2%80%93%20that%20would%20like%20the%20elections%20to%20be%20held%20by%20equivocating%20the%20issues%2C%20demands%20and%20requirements%20at%20the%20grassroots%20level%20with%20that%20of%20the%20intermediate%20and%2For%20national%20level%20%E2%80%93%20not%20for%20a%20federal%20democracy%20like%20India%20where%20the%20popular%20mandate%20would%20vary%20not%20only%20at%20each%20level%2C%20but%20also%20regionally.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EAjay%20K.%20Mehra%20is%20a%20political%20scientist.%20He%20was%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20Senior%20Fellow%2C%20Nehru%20Memorial%20Museum%20and%20Library%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%202019-21%20and%20Principal%2C%20Shaheed%20Bhagat%20Singh%20Evening%20College%2C%20Delhi%20University%20(2018).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711281973000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F29135301%2FScreenshot-2024-02-29-at-1.52.52-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsimultaneous-elections-will-be-a-blow-to-ind